<p>I agree with most of <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1605129394" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;">A Random Day</a></span>'s sentiments above, but I want to clarify a bit more about why I upvoted SCP-5555-EX and why I downvoted this.</p>
<p>I believe you're suffering from inverse issues between your two articles. In your original draft, the writing wasn't all that great, but the idea was very focused and constricted. You might recall in our DMs when I was critting SCP-5555-EX that I emphasized cutting certain points out and rewriting things to be more on-point: this was to contract your idea down to a single focus in order to have the reader follow a single line to its logical end (amnesticization causes deja vu; because deja vu is a common phenomenon and you have experienced deja vu&#8230;).</p>
<p>However, in this article, your idea is very wild and toys around with numerous different concepts. It jumps from amnesticization and deja vu to XK-Class Scenarios, parallel realities, precognition, and L33T SP34K (which I'm not a fan of personally and find slightly cliche). Nonetheless, the writing in many parts of the article flows like butter, which I find to be very satisfying and I congratulate you for managing to excel in your writing since the last I've looked at it.</p>
<p>My recommendation for this is to keep the original idea and use your new lexicon skills to rewrite the <em>execution</em> of 5555-EX, but not rewrite the idea. Your goal should be to maximize the horror and spell out enough that a reader will be able to dawn upon the conclusion with a bit of thinking, but not spell it outright. If you would like, I can help you more in DMs, since I'm certain you've got all the tools now to make this a stunning article.</p>

